    <stitle>DIAMONDLIFE&#8482; (BOSCH PIN SLIDE) DISC BRAKES For Vehicles Built After June 2, 2002 - DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Hydraulic pin slide disc brakes are two-piston sliding caliper brakes and are used at both front and
                rear wheels
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404701">(Figure 1</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404702">Figure 2)</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="f0404702"/>. The pin slide caliper disc brake is made up of four major components: caliper,
                anchor plate, rotor and disc brake pads.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0404701" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="472px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Hydraulic Pin Slide Disc Brake - Driver Side Front (73 mm)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CALIPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HYDRAULIC PISTON</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0404702" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Hydraulic Pin Slide Disc Brake - Driver Side Rear (73 mm)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CALIPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HYDRAULIC PISTON</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
